<font face="AnsiCRT"><font color="#5454FC">*</font><font color="#FC5454">Fruitbat the </font><font color="#A80000">slaugtering</font><font color="#FC5454"> wizard has just disappeared in a puff of smoke.</font></font>
</pre>
</td></tr>
</table>
<p>Apart from his <font color="#a80000">slaughtering</font> prefix, which is getting a bit cobwebby, it's all a bit uninspiring. Can you come up with something better?</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<ul>
<li>Fruitbat the jovial wizard bounds in.
<li>Grinning like a maniac Fruitbat the jovial wizard smirks at you.
<li>Fruitbat the jovial wizard flaps his arms around wildly.
<li>Fruitbat the jovial wizard laughs heartily then disappears before your eyes.
<li>You can hear a distant chuckle getting louder then Fruitbat the jovial wizard appears!
<li>Fruitbat the jovial wizard leaps out.
</ul>
<p>The person who comes up with the image that most suits Fruitbat wins himself or herself a free month, courtesy of Fruitbat!</p>
<p>Please send in your ideas before the next issue to <a href=mailto:editor@muddled-times.com>editor@muddled-times.com</a> in the format used in the above example.</p>
